{
  "texts": [
    "In addition to mid-infrared spectroscopy, Raman scattering spectroscopy can also be employed for analyzing molecular structures and chemical compositions.",
    "Ahmadivand et al. [222] utilized GA to design and optimize metasurfaces for surface-enhanced Raman scattering (SERS) substrates, enabling the detection of SARS-CoV-2 virus.",
    "To analyze the SERS data, the authors collected hundreds of Raman spectra from different samples.",
    "After preprocessing steps such as normalization, feature scaling, and Savitzky-Golay filtering, the data dimension was reduced using PCA algorithm.",
    "In the experiments, a supervised learning model, SVM, was trained using data from 15 PCR-positive samples and 12 PCR-negative samples for virus identification."
  ]
}